by being on myjury,

04:21.128 --> 04:23.119
- He was just picked today.
- Oh, yeah?

04:23.230 --> 04:25.061
He's got
this paint sale tomorrow.

04:25.165 --> 04:26.758
And he was hoping
that they'd let him off.

04:26.867 --> 04:28.892
Well, I'll tell you something.
He mentioned that to the judge.

04:29.002 --> 04:32.029
Now, by the way, what does, uh,
"in contempt of court" mean?

04:33.774 --> 04:35.071
It means he's gonna be
on the jury.

04:35.175 --> 04:36.233
Yeah, that's cool.

04:36.343 --> 04:37.810
Oh look, Fonz,
we're very excited

04:37.911 --> 04:39.174
about your-your being
picked and everything,

04:39.279 --> 04:40.974
- That's nice. -but we gotta
come up with a song.

04:41.081 --> 04:43.072
We got this song festival,
and we need one.

04:43.183 --> 04:45.652
Well, uh,
what's your favorite song?

04:47.053 --> 04:49.022
"America the Beautiful."

04:53.026 --> 04:56.155
<i>MARION: Hold it
right there, young lady.</i>

04:56.263 --> 04:57.628
