(QiQQHES)

05:07.007 --> 05:10.067
Well, you can't go hunk hunting
on an empty stomach.

05:10.177 --> 05:12.702
- Sit down.
- I'm late.

05:12.812 --> 05:14.610
Okay, all right.

05:14.714 --> 05:16.774
♪ We're three caballeros ♪

05:16.883 --> 05:19.375
♪ Three gay caballeros ♪

05:19.486 --> 05:22.080
♪ They say we are
birds of a feather ♪

05:22.189 --> 05:24.180
♪ Hup, hup, ho! ♪

05:28.895 --> 05:30.591
How about that?

05:30.697 --> 05:34.133
Great. Breakfast comes
with a floor show now.

05:34.234 --> 05:35.633
- Well...
- Now, Richard,

05:35.735 --> 05:37.135
would you like me
to fix you some eggs?

05:37.237 --> 05:38.432
Well, no, no, I don't have time.

05:38.538 --> 05:40.199
Potsie, Ralph and I
have to rehearse

05:40.307 --> 05:41.900
for this fraternity
song festival

05:42.008 --> 05:43.567
and that's why I'm doing
the-the caballero song...

05:43.677 --> 05:44.735
- Oh.
- ♪ We're three... ♪

05:44.844 --> 05:45.743
(doorbell rings)

05:45.845 --> 05:47.245
Oh, I'll get it, I'll get it.

05:47.347 --> 05:49.338
It's probably
Ted Mack for Richie.

05:49.449 --> 05:51.383
RICHIE:
Hey, you know something, Mom?

05:51.484 --> 05:52.747
(mocking):
You know something, Mom?

05:52.852 --> 05:54.218
Hi, Blue Eyes.

05:54.321 --> 05:57.381
I'm delivering a kiss-a-gram
for Joanie Cunningham.

05:57.490 --> 05:58.389
(laughs)

05:58.491 --> 06:00.960
Stamp it "return to sender."

06:01.061 --> 06:03.928
Aw, Chachi, can't you be subtle?

06:04.030 --> 06:06.499
Carrying your own blanket?

06:08.101 --> 06:09.000
It's not a blanket.

06:09.102 --> 06:10.331
It's a serape.

06:10.437 --> 06:11.802
I brought it for your brother.

06:11.905 --> 06:12.997
Oh.

06:13.106 --> 06:14.403
- Hey, Rich, here it is.
- Oh, Chachi, good.

06:14.507 --> 06:15.805
- Here, try it on.
- All right, here. Hey, good.

06:15.909 --> 06:18.105
- There you go.
- ♪ We're three caballeros... ♪

06:22.916 --> 06:24.076
What is this?

06:24.184 --> 06:26.414
It's a... it's a parrot.

06:26.519 --> 06:27.885
No, I can see that,
but what is it?

06:27.988 --> 06:29.785
It adds a little class.

06:29.889 --> 06:32.654
Yeah, and they're gonna need
all the class they can get.

06:32.759 --> 06:34.090
Don't you have to go to school?

06:34.194 --> 06:35.889
Oh, right! Good point.

06:35.996 --> 06:37.793
- MARION: Joanie?
- I'm eating my toast.

06:37.897 --> 06:39.763
Joanie!

06:39.866 --> 06:42.563
She didn't even touch this.

06:42.669 --> 06:43.659
Oh!

06:45.372 --> 06:46.305
Oh, Richard.

06:46.406 --> 06:48.670
Criminetly, dear.

06:48.775 --> 06:49.867
Well, I'll see you, everybody.

06:49.976 --> 06:51.842
I gotta go
to the library and study.

06:51.945 --> 06:53.435
Hunks?

06:53.546 --> 06:56.516
Hunkettes.

06:58.385 --> 07:00.717
Good morning, Richard.

07:00.820 --> 07:02.812
Hi, Dad.

07:05.392 --> 07:06.859
Where did you get that?

07:06.960 --> 07:08.928
Oh, well it, uh,
it came with the parrot.

07:09.029 --> 07:11.498
(laughs)
It came... with...

07:11.598 --> 07:13.999
No, we're doing this-this act,
"The Three Caballeros"

07:14.100 --> 07:15.864
for the fraternity
song festival.

07:15.969 --> 07:16.868
Oh, are parents invited?

07:16.970 --> 07:19.530
- No.
- Good.

07:19.639 --> 07:20.902
Fonzie here yet?

07:21.007 --> 07:23.169
We have to report for jury duty
in half an hour.

07:23.276 --> 07:25.506
Good, you'll have time
for a nice healthy breakfast.

07:25.612 --> 07:27.080
No, just coffee, Marion.

07:27.180 --> 07:28.944
I want to go over that list
of instructions

07:29.049 --> 07:30.607
I gave you
for the, uh, paint sale.

07:30.717 --> 07:32.082
Oh, Howard, forget this list.

07:32.185 --> 07:33.619
I can't read your writing.

07:33.720 --> 07:35.620
You mean to tell me you were
going to open up the store

07:35.722 --> 07:36.985
without checking that list?!

07:37.090 --> 07:37.989
Oh, Dad, take it easy.

07:38.091 --> 07:39.855
Mom's gonna do just fine.

07:39.959 --> 07:42.622
I don't need
any business advice from someone

07:42.729 --> 07:46.165
who carries a toy parrot
on his shoulder.

07:46.266 --> 07:48.530
Well, on that cheerful note,

07:48.635 --> 07:50.000
I'm gonna go.

07:50.103 --> 07:52.970
Adios, amigos.

07:53.073 --> 07:55.974
(squawks twice)

07:58.611 --> 08:01.080
- He's so funny.
- Oh.

08:01.181 --> 08:03.911
Hey, the very best
of good mornings, Mrs. C.

08:04.017 --> 08:05.075
How you doing?

08:05.185 --> 08:07.244
How are you,
fellow member of the jury?

08:10.156 --> 08:12.523
I want to tell you something,
I want to tell you something.

08:12.625 --> 08:14.059
I want, I want
all your attention

08:14.160 --> 08:16.925
right here
on myjudicial attire.

08:17.030 --> 08:18.862
Oh, Arthur,

08:18.965 --> 08:20.956
you look very nice.

08:21.501 --> 08:24.368
(laughs)

08:24.471 --> 08:26.234
Hey, thanks a lot.
I hope I don't look too nice.

08:26.339 --> 08:28.137
'Cause I don't want the judge
to mistake me for a lawyer,

08:28.241 --> 08:29.732
You know? Hey.

08:29.843 --> 08:31.868
Hey, since we're both going
to the courthouse,

08:31.978 --> 08:34.140
how about if I give you a ride
on my motorcycle?

08:34.246 --> 08:36.544
- No thanks, Fonz. -All right,
I promise, no wheelies.

08:36.649 --> 08:38.583
No, I'd just
as soon take my car.

08:38.684 --> 08:40.653
All right, then forget
about style, huh?

08:40.754 --> 08:41.846
Mrs. C!

08:41.955 --> 08:44.048
Where were you on the evening
of October 30?

08:44.157 --> 08:45.647
The whole truth, and nothing
but the truth, huh?

08:45.759 --> 08:48.159
Hey, I got this down.
This case is closed.

08:48.261 --> 08:50.127
Whoa!

08:51.598 --> 08:53.225
(gavel banging)

08:53.333 --> 08:56.098
Members of the jury, you've
heard both the prosecution

08:56.202 --> 08:57.932
and the defense
present their cases.

08:58.037 --> 08:59.938
And now, based on that evidence,

09:00.040 --> 09:02.304
it is time
for you to deliberate.

09:02.409 --> 09:04.673
- Why even bother?
-(gavel bangs)

09:04.778 --> 09:07.577
Will the defendant
please come to order?

09:07.680 --> 09:10.343
Maybe you'll get order,
but you won't get justice.

09:10.450 --> 09:12.851
Now, I didn't take her purse--
I keep telling you,

09:12.952 --> 09:14.579
-you got the wrong man.
-(gavel bangs)

09:14.687 --> 09:17.680
The bailiff will remove the
defendant from the courtroom.

09:17.791 --> 09:20.624
Look, I keep telling you,
a guy on a motorcycle

09:20.727 --> 09:23.423
dropped the purse
as he drove by me.

09:23.530 --> 09:27.330
Oh, why bother? You guys
got it in for cyclists, anyway.

09:27.434 --> 09:29.800
Aw, you want to take me out now?

09:29.903 --> 09:32.667
Those people really know
how to put on a show, huh?

09:32.772 --> 09:34.069
(gavel bangs)

09:34.174 --> 09:36.165
Ladies and gentlemen
of the jury,

09:36.276 --> 09:39.109
your decision should be based
solely upon the evidence.

09:39.212 --> 09:42.113
Please disregard
the defendant's remarks.

09:42.215 --> 09:45.082
Because of circumstances
beyond our control,

09:45.185 --> 09:47.085
the jury room is not available.

09:47.187 --> 09:51.180
So you'll have to remain here
to deliberate.

09:51.291 --> 09:53.191
This shouldn't take long.

09:53.293 --> 09:55.887
At this time,
the court will be in recess

09:55.995 --> 09:59.193
until such a time as the jury
finds the defendant,

09:59.299 --> 10:02.996
Jason Davis,
guilty or not guilty

10:03.103 --> 10:05.094
beyond any reasonable doubt.

10:05.205 --> 10:08.140
The bailiff
will clear the courtroom,

10:08.241 --> 10:09.140
except for the jury.

10:09.242 --> 10:10.232
(bangs gavel)

10:13.680 --> 10:15.978
Hey.

10:16.082 --> 10:17.846
- Eh!
- Oh...

10:21.688 --> 10:24.418
Five years I wanted
to get on a jury,

10:24.524 --> 10:26.652
and I get
a purse-snatching case.

10:26.759 --> 10:28.489
I wanted to do
the death penalty.

10:28.595 --> 10:30.085
I wanted fun.

10:31.598 --> 10:34.863
Well, we're real sorry
that we're spoiling your fun.

10:34.968 --> 10:37.095
A man's freedom
is on the line here.

10:37.203 --> 10:39.832
Aw, forget it. Let's get
this whole thing over with, huh?

10:39.939 --> 10:41.236
- Yeah...
- It's almost 5:00.

10:41.341 --> 10:44.140
Mr. Foreman, could you read
the votes so we can go home?

10:44.244 --> 10:46.235
We all know he's guilty.

10:46.346 --> 10:48.712
(low, indistinct chatter)

10:48.815 --> 10:52.911
What we have here
are 11 guilties...

10:53.019 --> 10:56.353
and one "not-guilty-a-mundo."

10:58.000 --> 11:04.074
